data.name: ans1
data.value: It is an easy-to-use service and you can benefit from it at home, at work or anywhere, all you have to do is enter the our website www.al-khaleejbank.com and choose the service.

data.name: ans11
data.value: Through the service, you can perform routine daily transactions and finding your account statement.

data.name: ans12
data.value: You can also make transfers, make top-ups and pay bills in addition to many other features.

data.name: ans32
data.value: Enter your data to access the Internet Banking Service.

data.name: ans33
data.value: Enter your password to log-in and enjoy all services we’re providing.

data.name: ans4
data.value: To complete the transfer between accounts, the system will automatically send “OTP” via your phone that’s linked to your account and all you have to do is enter the password to complete the process.

data.name: ans5
data.value: We’ve issued a unique password calls OTP (One Time Password) when you do the process of transferring between and to any account within Al-Khaleej Bank, the OTP is a safety factor to verify the integrity of your entry and to protect you from fraud via the Internet, which is a digital code issued and sent to you automatically by the system in the mobile number or your registered email address.

data.name: ans6
data.value: If you didn’t receive the OTP that could you for two reasons:

data.name: ans61
data.value: Delay causes from telecommunication (at this case please try again shortly).

data.name: ans62
data.value: Changing registered phone number or email (kindly update your details at your branch).

data.name: ans7
data.value: For reasons related to protecting your information and money, please do not disclose your password or write it down in a clear place.

data.name: ans71
data.value: You can change the password by using the following options:

data.name: ans72
data.value: Visit our website www.al-khaleejbank.com and click "Sign in" in the box for Internet Banking.

data.name: ans74
data.value: Enter the user name and account number and follow the instructions.

data.name: ans75
data.value: Enter the password that you will receive via your phone or email that’s registered with the bank

data.name: ans76
data.value: When entering the password, you will be given a temporary password for accessing the Internet Banking Service via your phone or email registered with the bank.

data.name: ans8
data.value: We apologize if you are facing difficulties in using the Internet Banking, you can contact us via e-mail: www.info@al-khaleejbank.com or by calling our call center at 7575.
